1
00:02:13,410 --> 00:02:15,850
Run for Young

2
00:02:44,450 --> 00:02:45,090
I got it!

3
00:02:45,810 --> 00:02:46,810
I know you got it.

4
00:02:46,810 --> 00:02:47,690
But what do you hit me for?

5
00:02:47,690 --> 00:02:49,650
I got it. We should sing as we want.

6
00:02:50,570 --> 00:02:51,170
And then?

7
00:02:51,450 --> 00:02:52,070
Then...

8
00:02:52,770 --> 00:02:54,450
Our school will hold

9
00:02:54,450 --> 00:02:55,370
New Year's Party?

10
00:02:55,970 --> 00:02:56,890
And?

11
00:02:56,890 --> 00:02:58,170
We'll be like them,

12
00:02:58,170 --> 00:02:59,010
going on the stage!

13
00:02:59,010 --> 00:03:00,090
And?

14
00:03:00,090 --> 00:03:02,330
And I'll bravely confess to Chen Yuanyuan!

15
00:03:04,410 --> 00:03:08,730
Screaming Glasses Noodles

16
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:10,370
It's late. I'm going home.

17
00:03:10,610 --> 00:03:11,610
I'll walk with you.

18
00:03:12,970 --> 00:03:14,410
Ma Tian and I head the same way.

19
00:03:14,410 --> 00:03:16,330
Ma Tian will help me with my homework.

20
00:03:18,370 --> 00:03:22,170
Episode 7 Love in a Lifetime

21
00:03:35,570 --> 00:03:36,450
Look.

22
00:03:36,970 --> 00:03:38,970
We end up here again.

23
00:03:46,050 --> 00:03:48,090
I wonder whether he's doing well there.

24
00:03:52,650 --> 00:03:54,250
Before, I tried hard,

25
00:03:54,890 --> 00:03:56,690
to fill the gap between us.

26
00:03:58,130 --> 00:03:59,730
However, I ended up going further.

27
00:04:01,730 --> 00:04:03,050
After you come out,

28
00:04:03,050 --> 00:04:04,170
you can restart everything.

29
00:04:07,970 --> 00:04:09,330
You're just a stupid dog.

30
00:04:11,490 --> 00:04:12,370
Time is over!

31
00:04:12,850 --> 00:04:14,650
You're in the same class, right?

32
00:04:17,930 --> 00:04:18,930
You still have a chance.

33
00:04:23,570 --> 00:04:24,610
I'm sure he's doing well.

34
00:04:26,370 --> 00:04:27,170
What's wrong?

35
00:04:29,530 --> 00:04:30,250
Nothing.

36
00:04:31,050 --> 00:04:32,210
Just a little uncomfortable.

37
00:04:36,010 --> 00:04:37,250
You're okay. Not a fever.

38
00:04:38,930 --> 00:04:40,010
I'm alright.

39
00:04:40,010 --> 00:04:41,010
Let's go home.

40
00:04:44,890 --> 00:04:45,810
Doggo,

41
00:04:47,090 --> 00:04:48,850
actually you're a nice person.

42
00:04:49,650 --> 00:04:50,930
Why do you suddenly say that?

43
00:04:52,330 --> 00:04:53,570
I just want to say,

44
00:04:54,010 --> 00:04:54,810
during this period...

45
00:04:54,810 --> 00:04:56,890
That's fine. We're classmates!

46
00:04:57,490 --> 00:04:58,970
Moreover, Liu Wenqin is my big brother.

47
00:04:59,410 --> 00:05:01,170
Otherwise, how could I care about you so much?

48
00:05:02,370 --> 00:05:04,130
I need to comfort you for him.

49
00:05:04,130 --> 00:05:05,250
Otherwise, you'll think,

50
00:05:05,250 --> 00:05:06,370
people like us

51
00:05:06,370 --> 00:05:07,450
aren't loyal to friends.

52
00:05:09,850 --> 00:05:10,650
Yes.

53
00:05:18,370 --> 00:05:19,250
Teaty just said

54
00:05:19,250 --> 00:05:20,890
we would sing in New Year's Party.

55
00:05:21,530 --> 00:05:22,610
Why did you refuse?

56
00:05:23,010 --> 00:05:23,810
That's bullshit.

57
00:05:24,410 --> 00:05:25,490
So scary.

58
00:05:26,090 --> 00:05:27,170
You're talking nonsense.

59
00:05:28,370 --> 00:05:30,050
I thought you wanted to be a Super Girl.

60
00:05:32,850 --> 00:05:33,610
How do you know that?

61
00:05:34,330 --> 00:05:35,450
I certainly know that.

62
00:05:35,970 --> 00:05:37,490
You were so absorbed in watching it.

63
00:05:41,010 --> 00:05:42,050
Do you think I can?

64
00:05:43,050 --> 00:05:43,810
Of course.

65
00:05:44,050 --> 00:05:44,730
Anyway,

66
00:05:45,370 --> 00:05:46,810
we need to find a song to practice.

67
00:05:46,810 --> 00:05:47,730
You're right.

68
00:05:47,730 --> 00:05:49,450
Anyway, we're not busy.

69
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:51,410
We can also ask Doggo and Anran to join.

70
00:05:52,130 --> 00:05:53,610
We become so close,

71
00:05:53,610 --> 00:05:54,570
just for them.

72
00:05:56,370 --> 00:05:57,650
Isn't it because you're happy with me?

73
00:05:57,650 --> 00:05:58,970
Even just a bit?

74
00:06:03,810 --> 00:06:05,130
So,

75
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:06,570
we become close,

76
00:06:06,970 --> 00:06:08,650
not just for others.

77
00:06:09,810 --> 00:06:11,130
So what's that for?

78
00:06:11,970 --> 00:06:13,050
For...

79
00:06:13,370 --> 00:06:15,010
Big Mouth.

80
00:06:15,970 --> 00:06:16,730
Big Mouth.

81
00:06:16,730 --> 00:06:17,410
Going on the stage.

82
00:06:18,250 --> 00:06:20,650
Teaty, why don't you ask Jiao?

83
00:06:20,890 --> 00:06:22,010
Don't you know

84
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:23,530
she's a terrible singer?

85
00:06:23,650 --> 00:06:24,810
I'm even worse.

86
00:06:25,330 --> 00:06:27,130
You're a little better than her.

87
00:06:28,610 --> 00:06:29,410
Got a cold?

88
00:06:29,930 --> 00:06:30,810
No.

89
00:06:31,690 --> 00:06:33,690
There must be someone cursing me.

90
00:06:33,930 --> 00:06:35,170
Such a big girl like you

91
00:06:35,170 --> 00:06:36,330
still believes such nonsense?

92
00:06:40,930 --> 00:06:42,610
What are you doing? I want to sleep.

93
00:06:42,850 --> 00:06:45,250
I won't let you go if you don't promise me!

94
00:06:46,370 --> 00:06:47,010
Okay.

95
00:06:48,130 --> 00:06:49,450
I can do that.

96
00:06:53,050 --> 00:06:54,050
This one

97
00:06:54,930 --> 00:06:55,970
costs 80.

98
00:06:56,210 --> 00:06:56,970
What?

99
00:06:57,490 --> 00:06:58,570
Rise again?

100
00:06:58,810 --> 00:07:00,290
This is the ultimate version.

101
00:07:01,250 --> 00:07:02,090
Don't you feel

102
00:07:02,090 --> 00:07:03,210
Chen Yuanyuan and you

103
00:07:03,210 --> 00:07:04,850
become closer?

104
00:07:07,090 --> 00:07:07,930
No.

105
00:07:08,250 --> 00:07:08,890
That's fine.

106
00:07:09,290 --> 00:07:11,010
What if she says yes

107
00:07:11,010 --> 00:07:11,690
after you buy the book

108
00:07:11,890 --> 00:07:12,530
go on the stage,

109
00:07:12,530 --> 00:07:13,810
perform

110
00:07:14,610 --> 00:07:17,210
and confess to her?

111
00:07:24,810 --> 00:07:25,530
Big Mouth,

112
00:07:26,690 --> 00:07:27,370
100 yuan.

113
00:07:27,610 --> 00:07:28,530
Keep the change.

114
00:07:28,650 --> 00:07:29,250
Thanks.

115
00:07:32,170 --> 00:07:32,930
Big Mouth.

116
00:07:33,410 --> 00:07:34,210
My dear brother.

117
00:07:45,770 --> 00:07:46,890
You wear so little.

118
00:07:48,530 --> 00:07:49,730
Want to commit suicide?

119
00:07:50,210 --> 00:07:52,210
I don't have money to send you to hospital.

120
00:07:52,530 --> 00:07:53,770
I'm thinking about life.

121
00:07:54,530 --> 00:07:55,930
Why do you think about

122
00:07:55,930 --> 00:07:58,250
what you don't own?

123
00:07:59,530 --> 00:08:00,450
Why don't I own it?

124
00:08:02,850 --> 00:08:04,530
You're going to die for love.

125
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:11,050
Every John has his Joan.

126
00:08:12,050 --> 00:08:14,410
You'll find your Joan one day.

127
00:08:16,370 --> 00:08:17,810
Why don't you find

128
00:08:17,810 --> 00:08:19,490
yours?

129
00:08:23,090 --> 00:08:24,890
Someone like me,

130
00:08:24,890 --> 00:08:25,890
you think I

131
00:08:25,890 --> 00:08:27,650
can't find one if I really want to?

132
00:08:27,850 --> 00:08:28,690
It's all because of...

133
00:08:28,690 --> 00:08:29,810
None of my business.

134
00:08:32,850 --> 00:08:33,650
Alright.

135
00:08:44,250 --> 00:08:45,010
Here's the notice.

136
00:08:45,330 --> 00:08:47,130
We'll still have a new year's party

137
00:08:47,210 --> 00:08:48,290
this year.

138
00:08:48,410 --> 00:08:49,810
Each class shall give a performance.

139
00:08:50,330 --> 00:08:51,970
We're in the senior year.

140
00:08:52,450 --> 00:08:53,770
I'm sure there won't be many

141
00:08:53,770 --> 00:08:55,170
having the mood for it.

142
00:08:55,490 --> 00:08:56,090
I do!

143
00:08:57,250 --> 00:08:58,450
Of course, you do.

144
00:08:58,490 --> 00:08:59,930
What a splendid life you have.

145
00:09:01,290 --> 00:09:03,050
I want to find a companion from mortal world,

146
00:09:03,050 --> 00:09:04,210
and have an unrestrained life.

147
00:09:04,490 --> 00:09:05,490
Is that wrong?

148
00:09:05,730 --> 00:09:06,330
Okay.

149
00:09:06,690 --> 00:09:07,570
In that case...

150
00:09:08,050 --> 00:09:09,490
Please don't approve him, madam.

151
00:09:10,810 --> 00:09:11,890
I also have a performance to give, madam.

152
00:09:12,810 --> 00:09:13,690
Whose your partner?

153
00:09:14,010 --> 00:09:14,609
She.

154
00:09:14,609 --> 00:09:15,490
Not me!

155
00:09:16,130 --> 00:09:16,890
Madam,

156
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:17,849
before graduation,

157
00:09:17,849 --> 00:09:18,969
we dance team,

158
00:09:18,969 --> 00:09:20,450
also want to perform on the stage.

159
00:09:20,609 --> 00:09:21,229
Okay.

160
00:09:21,330 --> 00:09:22,570
You can compete for this.

161
00:09:22,849 --> 00:09:24,290
Anyway, we can only give one performance.

162
00:09:24,690 --> 00:09:26,170
I haven't decided it yet.

163
00:09:26,370 --> 00:09:27,370
What are you scared of? Just have a try.

164
00:09:27,730 --> 00:09:28,370
I can't.

165
00:09:28,370 --> 00:09:29,330
Ma Tian.

166
00:09:29,530 --> 00:09:30,130
How about

167
00:09:30,210 --> 00:09:31,410
going on the stage with me?

168
00:09:33,650 --> 00:09:35,770
You don't want to perform

169
00:09:35,770 --> 00:09:37,450
with a coward, right?

170
00:09:37,810 --> 00:09:38,410
So,

171
00:09:38,810 --> 00:09:40,050
you work together,

172
00:09:40,050 --> 00:09:40,970
or separately?

173
00:09:41,290 --> 00:09:42,330
Separately!

174
00:09:42,330 --> 00:09:43,610
We work together, madam!

175
00:09:44,970 --> 00:09:45,690
I'll leave it to you.

176
00:09:45,770 --> 00:09:47,330
You decide

177
00:09:47,730 --> 00:09:48,490
by yourselves.

178
00:09:48,770 --> 00:09:50,490
Why do I become a coward?

179
00:09:51,010 --> 00:09:52,210
You certainly aren't.

180
00:09:52,770 --> 00:09:53,890
That's why you should sing on the stage.

181
00:10:02,850 --> 00:10:05,650
Have you ever thought

182
00:10:06,210 --> 00:10:07,090
about beating

183
00:10:07,410 --> 00:10:08,450
drum

184
00:10:08,730 --> 00:10:10,210
on the stage

185
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:12,290
in front of the audience one day?

186
00:10:13,730 --> 00:10:14,330
No.

187
00:10:15,730 --> 00:10:17,170
That's right.

188
00:10:17,730 --> 00:10:18,930
Then come to the stage with us.

189
00:10:19,090 --> 00:10:20,130
Because we never thought

190
00:10:20,130 --> 00:10:21,050
about that either.

191
00:10:22,130 --> 00:10:22,730
Which day?

192
00:10:23,370 --> 00:10:24,210
New Year's Party.

193
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:26,090
New Year's Party.

194
00:10:27,490 --> 00:10:28,210
Can we do it?

195
00:10:29,370 --> 00:10:30,930
Have you sung the song of John Lennon?

196
00:10:32,010 --> 00:10:32,730
He once sang

197
00:10:33,730 --> 00:10:35,530
"You may say I'm a dreamer.

198
00:10:35,570 --> 00:10:36,450
But

199
00:10:37,130 --> 00:10:38,410
I'm not the only one."

200
00:10:41,010 --> 00:10:42,210
You mean this song?

201
00:10:43,290 --> 00:10:47,410
♪ You may say I'm a dreamer ♪

202
00:10:47,410 --> 00:10:48,890
Right. That's it.

203
00:10:49,130 --> 00:10:50,050
So we'll sing

204
00:10:50,050 --> 00:10:51,210
the song of John Lennon?

205
00:10:51,290 --> 00:10:51,890
Yes!

206
00:10:51,970 --> 00:10:53,530
New Butterfly Dream!

207
00:11:03,010 --> 00:11:03,810
Let me think it through.

208
00:11:09,930 --> 00:11:10,930
Tell me

209
00:11:11,490 --> 00:11:12,730
if you really like playing drum that much?

210
00:11:13,770 --> 00:11:15,810
I don't usually have a good drum to play.

211
00:11:16,650 --> 00:11:17,610
My performance depends.

212
00:11:18,770 --> 00:11:19,490
And...

213
00:11:20,330 --> 00:11:21,050
And,

214
00:11:21,050 --> 00:11:22,850
you think Teaty is unreliable.

215
00:11:22,850 --> 00:11:23,610
Am I right?

216
00:11:23,850 --> 00:11:24,650
Why unreliable?

217
00:11:25,570 --> 00:11:26,330
He's

218
00:11:26,690 --> 00:11:27,570
certainly unreliable.

219
00:11:28,890 --> 00:11:30,650
And you still want to go on the stage with him?

220
00:11:31,050 --> 00:11:33,290
Cheers and thunderous applause

221
00:11:33,290 --> 00:11:33,970
are not something we must win.

222
00:11:35,050 --> 00:11:35,850
I've thought about it.

223
00:11:36,450 --> 00:11:37,410
With him,

224
00:11:37,650 --> 00:11:39,370
how could we impress people?

225
00:11:39,570 --> 00:11:40,250
However,

226
00:11:41,370 --> 00:11:42,050
we can't let him

227
00:11:42,050 --> 00:11:43,530
lose face alone.

228
00:11:45,050 --> 00:11:46,170
We're friends.

229
00:11:46,810 --> 00:11:48,050
I must accompany him.

230
00:11:55,810 --> 00:11:56,810
Mother,

231
00:11:57,290 --> 00:11:58,970
you got home early today.

232
00:11:59,370 --> 00:12:00,170
Yeah. You're back, Jie.

233
00:12:00,770 --> 00:12:01,730
Here, come with me.

234
00:12:04,730 --> 00:12:05,370
Look.

235
00:12:14,970 --> 00:12:15,690
Mom,

236
00:12:16,890 --> 00:12:18,850
you need to sell a lot of fruits to buy it.

237
00:12:20,810 --> 00:12:21,970
No matter what,

238
00:12:22,530 --> 00:12:24,490
you can finally play the real drum.

239
00:12:25,930 --> 00:12:26,530
Mom,

240
00:12:28,170 --> 00:12:28,810
I'll try it.

241
00:12:39,570 --> 00:12:40,570
I don't expect

242
00:12:40,890 --> 00:12:42,330
the sound of it is to be so loud.

243
00:12:43,490 --> 00:12:45,690
Our neighbors won't bear it.

244
00:12:48,290 --> 00:12:49,010
Mom,

245
00:12:50,290 --> 00:12:51,250
return it.

246
00:12:51,930 --> 00:12:53,090
It's a waste of money.

247
00:13:05,010 --> 00:13:05,730
Jiao Jiao,

248
00:13:05,930 --> 00:13:06,930
you're the only one I love.

249
00:13:07,410 --> 00:13:10,250
You are my super star.

250
00:13:12,850 --> 00:13:13,570
Jiao,

251
00:13:14,170 --> 00:13:15,410
do you know that,

252
00:13:15,410 --> 00:13:16,770
when I was young,

253
00:13:16,850 --> 00:13:18,610
I almost became a singer.

254
00:13:20,890 --> 00:13:21,490
I heard

255
00:13:21,490 --> 00:13:23,050
that you planned to debut at Shibati.

256
00:13:24,450 --> 00:13:25,770
Then I had you.

257
00:13:26,370 --> 00:13:27,730
So I gave up music,

258
00:13:27,930 --> 00:13:29,090
and started cooking noodles.

259
00:13:30,090 --> 00:13:31,810
However, I have a great dream.

260
00:13:32,290 --> 00:13:33,890
It's for you to go on pursuing my unfulfilled wish.

261
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:34,890
No.

262
00:13:35,370 --> 00:13:36,450
I mean, my unfinished cause.

263
00:13:37,290 --> 00:13:39,450
And become a great singer.

264
00:13:40,210 --> 00:13:41,730
Really?

265
00:13:42,890 --> 00:13:44,690
Then why am I out of tune?

266
00:13:48,690 --> 00:13:49,770
For singing,

267
00:13:50,610 --> 00:13:52,330
what matters is your mood.

268
00:13:53,410 --> 00:13:54,930
Who do you sing with

269
00:13:55,570 --> 00:13:56,570
and who do you sing for?

270
00:13:57,610 --> 00:13:59,130
It has nothing to do

271
00:13:59,290 --> 00:14:00,370
with whether you have a beautiful voice

272
00:14:02,210 --> 00:14:03,010
or in tune or not.

273
00:14:06,970 --> 00:14:07,730
I'll cook noodles.

274
00:14:26,410 --> 00:14:27,030
Mom,

275
00:14:27,970 --> 00:14:29,090
what are you doing?

276
00:14:31,230 --> 00:14:31,850
I really

277
00:14:32,250 --> 00:14:33,090
don't know

278
00:14:33,090 --> 00:14:34,210
what to do.

279
00:14:34,690 --> 00:14:35,650
So I try this

280
00:14:36,130 --> 00:14:37,050
for sound insulation.

281
00:14:38,890 --> 00:14:39,690
Mom,

282
00:14:40,930 --> 00:14:42,330
sit here.

283
00:14:42,650 --> 00:14:43,730
Be careful.

284
00:14:43,730 --> 00:14:46,450
I can do such a thing myself.

285
00:14:47,450 --> 00:14:48,250
It's okay.

286
00:14:49,050 --> 00:14:49,730
Mom.

287
00:14:56,730 --> 00:14:57,370
What's wrong

288
00:14:58,410 --> 00:14:59,530
with you?

289
00:15:03,710 --> 00:15:04,330
Mom,

290
00:15:06,690 --> 00:15:07,850
come to watch our performance

291
00:15:09,050 --> 00:15:10,010
at the New Year's Party.

292
00:15:12,290 --> 00:15:12,890
Really?

293
00:15:15,610 --> 00:15:16,650
Really.

294
00:15:18,450 --> 00:15:19,250
Okay.

295
00:15:19,450 --> 00:15:20,970
I'll go.

296
00:15:25,810 --> 00:15:26,970
I hope this party can

297
00:15:27,450 --> 00:15:28,970
be a happy ending to my unrequited love for Chen Yuanyuan

298
00:15:29,370 --> 00:15:31,530
